Enum BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod

    public static enum BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod
extends java.lang.Enum<BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod>
    Represents a traversal method that can be used to iterate over a binary search tree.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Joshua Gleitze

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      IN_ORDER
      Traverses the left subtree recursively, then outputs the node and traverses the right subtree recursively afterwards.
      LEVEL_ORDER
      Returns the elements on one level of the tree from left to right and continues with the next level afterwards.
      PRE_ORDER
      Outputs the node, then traverses the left subtree recursively and traverses the right subtree recursevly afterwards.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • IN_ORDER

        public static final BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod IN_ORDER
        Traverses the left subtree recursively, then outputs the node and traverses the right subtree recursively afterwards. Starts at the root of the tree.
        See Also:
        In order traversal on Wikipedia

      • LEVEL_ORDER

        public static final BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod LEVEL_ORDER
        Returns the elements on one level of the tree from left to right and continues with the next level afterwards. Starts at the root of the tree.
        See Also:
        Breath width first search on Wikipedia

      • PRE_ORDER

        public static final BinarySearchTree.TraversalMethod PRE_ORDER
        Outputs the node, then traverses the left subtree recursively and traverses the right subtree recursevly afterwards. Start at the root of the tree.
        See Also:
        Pre order traversal on Wikipedia
